{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775828261887,"sessionID":"ses_288658867ffeYP8HkBIcDuKaNV","part":{"id":"prt_d779a9595001yicuZE6HYcJJqU","messageID":"msg_d779a8397001vp2D4BFYvtVk8N","sessionID":"ses_288658867ffeYP8HkBIcDuKaNV","type":"tool","tool":"task","callID":"call_cf6c24038e3d408d81ef061c","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"description":"Explore agentcube project structure","prompt":"Explore the agentcube project at /home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z to understand:\n\n1. The overall project structure - what directories exist, what's the project about\n2. The pkg/router module specifically - what files exist, what does it do currently\n3. Any existing session management code or patterns\n4. How the client-go library (from the specs) relates to the router\n5. Any existing proposal.md or design docs for reference on format/style\n\nReturn a comprehensive summary of:\n- Project overview (what is agentcube?)\n- Current pkg/router implementation details (file paths, key functions, architecture)\n- Any session-related code patterns found\n- How AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter CRDs are used\n- Existing proposal.md format if found","subagent_type":"explore"},"output":"task_id: ses_2886551d5ffelrY2tilMkKcnPt (for resuming to continue this task if needed)\n\n<task_result>\nI now have a thorough understanding of the project. Here is the comprehensive summary:\n\n---\n\n## Comprehensive Project Summary: AgentCube\n\n### 1. Project Overview\n\n**AgentCube** is a Kubernetes-native sandbox orchestration platform for AI agents. It is hosted at `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube` and is part of the Volcano ecosystem.\n\n**Core Purpose:** Provisions isolated sandbox pods on demand, routes HTTP traffic to them through session-aware proxies, and manages their full lifecycle (creation, expiry, idle cleanup).\n\n**Architecture:**\n```\nClient / SDK / CLI\n  -> Router (Deployment :8080)\n     <-> Redis/Valkey (session store)\n     -> WorkloadManager (Service :8080)\n        <-> Redis/Valkey\n        -> K8s API: CRDs, Sandbox, Pod, Secret, TokenReview\n  Sandbox Pods (with optional PicoD daemon)\n  Agentd (idle cleanup controller)\n  Optional: Volcano vc-agentScheduler\n```\n\n**Tech Stack:**\n- **Server:** Go 1.25.0, module `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube`\n- **HTTP Framework:** Gin\n- **Kubernetes:** CRDs (`runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1`), controller-runtime, `sigs.k8s.io/agent-sandbox`\n- **Storage:** Redis (go-redis/v9), Valkey (valkey-go)\n- **Auth:** JWT RS256 (golang-jwt/v5), K8s TokenReview\n- **Packaging:** Helm 3, multi-stage Docker, GitHub Actions CI/CD\n\n---\n\n### 2. Current `pkg/router` Implementation Details\n\n**Location:** `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/pkg/router/`\n\n**Files (12 total):**\n\n| File | Purpose | Key Contents |\n|------|---------|-------------|\n| `config.go` | Configuration | `Config` struct (Port, Debug, EnableTLS, TLSCert, TLSKey, MaxConcurrentRequests), `NewDefaultConfig()` |\n| `server.go` | HTTP Server | `Server` struct, `NewServer()`, `Start()`, `Run()`, `Shutdown()`, route registration |\n| `session_manager.go` | Session resolution | `SessionManager` interface, `manager` impl, `GetSandboxBySession()`, `createSandbox()` via WorkloadManager HTTP calls |\n| `proxy.go` | Reverse proxy | `handleInvoke()`, `handleAgentInvoke()`, `handleCodeInterpreterInvoke()`, `forwardToSandbox()`, JWT injection, error mapping |\n| `jwt.go` | JWT management | `JWTManager` struct, RSA 2048-bit key generation, RS256 signing, K8s Secret store/load (`picod-router-identity`) |\n| `backend.go` | Backend health | `Backend` struct, `BackendHealthChecker` with configurable thresholds, HTTP `/health` probe |\n| `loadbalancer.go` | Load balancing | `LoadBalancer` interface, `RoundRobinBalancer`, `LeastConnectionsBalancer` with atomic counters |\n| `middleware.go` | HTTP middleware | `ConcurrencyLimitMiddleware` (semaphore), `RequestLoggerMiddleware`, `TraceIDMiddleware` |\n| `informer.go` | CRD informers | `InformerManager` with `SharedInformerFactory`, event handlers for AgentRuntime/CodeInterpreter (stub implementations - only log) |\n| `health.go` | Health endpoints | `handleHealthLive` (always 200), `handleHealthReady` (checks session manager) |\n| `errors.go` | Custom errors | `SessionNotFoundError`, `SandboxTemplateNotFoundError` |\n| `router.go` | Router interface (standalone) | `Router` interface, `routerImpl` with route map + load balancer (NOTE: this is a separate, simpler router NOT currently integrated into Server) |\n\n**Server Architecture:**\n\nThe `Server` struct is the central orchestrator:\n```go\ntype Server struct {\n    config         *Config\n    engine         *gin.Engine\n    httpServer     *http.Server\n    sessionManager SessionManager\n    storeClient    store.Store\n    httpTransport  *http.Transport\n    jwtManager     *JWTManager\n}\n```\n\n**Route Table:**\n| Method | Path | Handler |\n|--------|------|---------|\n| GET | `/health/live` | `handleHealthLive` |\n| GET | `/health/ready` | `handleHealthReady` |\n| GET, POST | `/v1/namespaces/:namespace/agent-runtimes/:name/invocations/*path` | `handleAgentInvoke` |\n| GET, POST | `/v1/namespaces/:namespace/code-interpreters/:name/invocations/*path` | `handleCodeInterpreterInvoke` |\n\n**Request Flow:**\n1. Request arrives at `/v1/namespaces/:namespace/agent-runtimes/:name/invocations/*path`\n2. Extract `x-agentcube-session-id` header\n3. If session ID present: look up `SandboxInfo` from store\n4. If session ID empty: POST to WorkloadManager to create sandbox\n5. Select entry point from `SandboxInfo.EntryPoints` by path prefix match\n6. Generate JWT (for Sandbox/SandboxClaim kinds), inject `Authorization: Bearer`\n7. Reverse proxy to sandbox pod via `httputil.ReverseProxy`\n8. Set response header `x-agentcube-session-id`\n9. Update `LastActivityAt` in store (before and after proxy)\n\n---\n\n### 3. Session Management Code Patterns\n\n**SessionManager Interface** (`session_manager.go`, line 19-21):\n```go\ntype SessionManager interface {\n    GetSandboxBySession(ctx context.Context, sessionID string, namespace string, name string, kind string) (*types.SandboxInfo, error)\n}\n```\n\n**Session Resolution Logic** (`session_manager.go`, lines 56-69):\n- If `sessionID` is non-empty: query `store.GetSandbox(ctx, sessionID)`\n  - On `store.ErrNotFound` -> return `SessionNotFoundError`\n- If `sessionID` is empty: call `createSandbox()` which POSTs to WorkloadManager\n  - AgentRuntime -> `{WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL}/v1/agent-runtime`\n  - CodeInterpreter -> `{WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL}/v1/code-interpreter`\n\n**SandboxInfo Model** (`pkg/workloadmanager/handler/models.go`, lines 53-66):\n```go\ntype SandboxInfo struct {\n    SessionID      string       `json:\"sessionId\"`\n    SandboxName    string       `json:\"sandboxName\"`\n    SandboxID      string       `json:\"sandboxId\"`\n    WorkloadName   string       `json:\"workloadName\"`\n    Namespace      string       `json:\"namespace\"`\n    Kind           string       `json:\"kind\"`\n    PodIP          string       `json:\"podIp,omitempty\"`\n    EntryPoints    []EntryPoint `json:\"entryPoints,omitempty\"`\n    CreatedAt      time.Time    `json:\"createdAt\"`\n    ExpiresAt      time.Time    `json:\"expiresAt\"`\n    Status         string       `json:\"status\"`\n    LastActivityAt time.Time    `json:\"lastActivityAt\"`\n}\n```\n\n**Store Interface** (`pkg/store/store.go`):\n```go\ntype Store interface {\n    StoreSandbox(ctx, sessionID string, info *SandboxInfo) error\n    UpdateSandbox(ctx, sessionID string, info *SandboxInfo) error\n    DeleteSandboxBySessionID(ctx, sessionID string) error\n    GetSandbox(ctx, sessionID string) (*SandboxInfo, error)\n    ListSandboxes(ctx) (map[string]*SandboxInfo, error)\n    UpdateSessionLastActivity(ctx, sessionID string, lastActivityTime interface{}) error\n}\n```\nNote: The current `Storage()` function returns `nil` -- the actual Redis/Valkey implementations are stubbed.\n\n**Session Lifecycle (GC)** is handled by `LifecycleManager` in `pkg/workloadmanager/handler/sandbox_lifecycle.go`:\n- TTL-based expiry cleanup\n- Idle timeout cleanup (default 15 minutes)\n- Orphan CR scan (CRs without store entries)\n- Ghost entry cleanup (store entries without CRs)\n\n---\n\n### 4. How client-go Library Relates to the Router\n\n**client-go Location:** `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/client-go/`\n\n**Structure:**\n```\nclient-go/\n  clientset/\n    clientset.go           -> Interface with RuntimeV1alpha1()\n    typed/runtime/v1alpha1/\n      interfaces.go        -> AgentRuntimeInterface, CodeInterpreterInterface (CRUD ops)\n      runtime_client.go    -> Typed client implementation\n  informers/\n    externalversions/\n      factory.go           -> SharedInformerFactory (wrapper around k8s.io/client-go informers)\n      runtime/interface.go -> Interface -> V1alpha1()\n      runtime/v1alpha1/interface.go -> AgentRuntimeInformer, CodeInterpreterInformer\n  listers/\n    runtime/v1alpha1/\n      expansion_generated.go -> AgentRuntimeLister, CodeInterpreterLister (cached reads)\n```\n\n**CRD Types** (`pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/`):\n- **AgentRuntime**: Defines sandbox template (PodSpec), ports, session timeout, max session duration\n- **CodeInterpreter**: Similar but with additional fields like `WarmPoolSize`, `AuthMode`, simplified template (image, env, command, args, resources)\n\n**How the Router Uses client-go:**\n\n1. **InformerManager** (`informer.go`) uses:\n   - `client-go/clientset.Interface` to create informers\n   - `client-go/informers/externalversions.SharedInformerFactory` for watching CRD changes\n   - `AgentRuntimeInformer` and `CodeInterpreterInformer` with event handlers\n   - Currently, the event handlers are **stubs** -- they only log at V(4) level and do NOT update any routing table\n\n2. **The `router.go` Router interface** is defined but **NOT integrated** into the Server. The Server uses Gin routes directly with `handleAgentInvoke`/`handleCodeInterpreterInvoke` which resolve sandboxes via the store + WorkloadManager, not via the `Router` interface.\n\n3. **The gap**: The InformerManager is constructed but never started or wired into the Server. The `routerImpl` in `router.go` has `AddRoute`/`RemoveRoute` but no code populates it from informer events. This is the unfinished work that AR-009/AR-010 are meant to address.\n\n---\n\n### 5. Existing proposal.md Format\n\n**Location examples:**\n- `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-009/proposal.md`\n- `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-010/proposal.md`\n\n**Template structure:**\n```markdown\n# AR-XXX: <Title>\n\n## Overview\n<!-- TODO: 填写变更概述 -->\n\n## 元信息\n- **AR**: AR-XXX — <Title>\n- **Module**: pkg/<module>\n- **Language**: Go\n- **Size**: M\n\n## 目的\n<!-- TODO: 填写变更目的 -->\n\n## 范围\n### 包含\n### 不包含\n\n## 影响分析\n### 直接影响\n### 下游依赖（本变更完成后解锁）\n### 无影响的组件\n\n## 备选方案\n<!-- TODO: 填写备选方案 -->\n\n## 验收标准\n<!-- TODO: 填写验收标准 -->\n\n## 状态\n- [ ] 提案审查\n- [ ] 实现\n- [ ] 验证\n```\n\n**The corresponding design.md template** (`changes/AR-010/design.md`):\n```markdown\n# AR-XXX: <Title> -- Design\n\n## 1. Architecture\n### 1.1 Positioning\n### 1.2 Package Structure\n### 1.3 Dependencies\n\n## 2. Data Structures\n## 3. API Contract\n## 4. Error Handling\n## 5. Testing Strategy\n## 6. Implementation Steps\n## 7. Future Changes\n```\n\n**Note:** The root-level `proposal.md` and `design.md` (for AR-009) are fully filled out and serve as excellent reference examples of completed documentation. The `changes/AR-010/proposal.md` and `changes/AR-010/design.md` are skeleton templates with TODO placeholders.\n</task_result>","metadata":{"sessionId":"ses_2886551d5ffelrY2tilMkKcnPt","model":{"modelID":"qwen3.6-plus","providerID":"alibaba-cn"},"truncated":false},"title":"Explore agentcube project structure","time":{"start":1775828119077,"end":1775828261884}}}}
